# LAN-only HTTPS front door for the Pi API.
#
# Caddy terminates TLS using its built-in *local* CA (`tls internal`) — no
# Let's Encrypt, no public domain, no internet needed. Devices trust it by
# installing Caddy's root CA once (see ai/lan-https-caddy-setup.md).
#
# The name must match the Pi-hole Local DNS record (pi.home.arpa -> Pi LAN IP)
# and the URL set in the PWA's "Local" field (https://pi.home.arpa:8443).
# Host port is 8443 (Tailscale Funnel holds the Pi's :443); Caddy still listens
# on 443 inside the container and matches by hostname, so no change here.
#
# This is a second, LAN-only front door; the Tailscale Funnel still serves the
# same api:8080 for off-LAN ("Remote") access, unchanged.
pi.home.arpa {
	tls internal
	reverse_proxy api:8080
}
